    • Constructor Detail

      • TodoItem

        public TodoItem(java.lang.String newTaskName,
                java.util.Date newStartDate,
                java.util.Date newEndDate,
                java.lang.String newPriority,
                java.lang.Boolean newDoneStatus)
        The standard constructor of a TodoItem. Upon calling this method, an immutable UUID will be assigned to the TodoItem.
        Parameters:
        newTaskName - The task name of the new task. Can be null.
        newStartDate - The start date of the new task. Can be null.
        newEndDate - The end date of the new task. Can be null.
        newPriority - The priority of the new task. Can be null. If not HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW, the new task's priority will be set at MEDIUM.
        newDoneStatus - The done status of the new task. Can be null. If null, the new task's priority will be set at false.

      • TodoItem

        public TodoItem(java.lang.String newTaskName,
                java.util.Date newStartDate,
                java.util.Date newEndDate)
        Auxiliary constructor for a TodoItem, requiring only the start date and end date. The priority is assumed to be MEDIUM, while the done status is assumed to be false.
        Parameters:
        newTaskName - The task name of the new item. Can be null.
        newStartDate - The start date of the new item. Can be null.
        newEndDate - The end date of the new item. Can be null.
